# Feature Implementation Guidelines

## Check Feature Status First

**Before implementing any feature**, check the documentation:

1. **Business Requirements:** Check [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for:
   - Business rules and workflows
   - User journeys and expected behavior
   - Data model and validation rules
   - Feature specifications and acceptance criteria

2. **Implementation Status:** Check the project README for feature status and roadmap
   - Implementation status (Complete, In Progress, Planned)
   - Feature dependencies and related components
   - Priority level and timeline
   - Known limitations or planned enhancements

## Implemented Features (DO NOT BREAK)

### Core Workflows

- **Board** (/board) - Drag & drop, real-time status updates
- **Session completion** - Post-treatment modal, body location selector (`/sessions` API)
- **Day Finalization Workflow** - End-of-day processing with undo
- **Patient Management** (/patients) - CRUD operations, patient details
- **Walk-In Check-In** - Unscheduled patient registration
- **Calendar & Scheduling** (/schedule) - Monthly/weekly views

### Cross-Cutting Features

- **Timezone Support** - 12 timezones, browser detection, localStorage persistence
- **Form Handling** - Client-side validation, Portuguese error messages
- **Error Handling** - Error boundaries, loading states, retry mechanisms

## Feature-Specific Rules

### Board

Key files:

- [AttendanceBoard](mdc:src/features/board/AttendanceBoard.tsx)
- [useDragAndDrop.ts](mdc:src/features/board/hooks/useDragAndDrop.ts)
- [attendanceStore.ts](mdc:src/stores/attendanceStore.ts)

Rules:

- Maintain drag-and-drop functionality
- Keep combined treatment handling (physiotherapy + tens move together)
- Preserve priority system (Emergency=1, Intermediate=2, Normal=3)
- Maintain patient grouping logic

### Patient Management

Key files:

- [Patient form](mdc:src/features/patients/form)
- [Patient detail](mdc:src/features/patients/detail)
- [usePatientQueries.ts](mdc:src/api/query/hooks/usePatientQueries.ts)

Rules:

- Validate all patient data before submission
- Support Portuguese error messages
- Maintain treatment recommendations workflow
- Keep attendance history integration

## Adding New Features

1. **Understand requirements** - Read [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for business context and workflows
2. **Check patterns** - Review [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for similar implementations
3. **Verify status** - Check the project README to avoid duplicating work
4. **Follow architecture** - Use established patterns from [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)
5. **Write tests** - Cover new or changed behavior with focused tests
6. **Test integration** - Ensure no breaking changes to existing features
7. **Update docs** - Update the project README with new feature status

## Feature Testing Checklist

Before considering a feature complete:

- [ ] Unit tests for all components and hooks
- [ ] Integration tests for feature workflows
- [ ] Error states and edge cases handled
- [ ] Loading states implemented
- [ ] Mobile responsive (ongoing)
- [ ] TypeScript strict mode passing
- [ ] No console errors or warnings
- [ ] Documentation updated

## Feature Dependencies

Some features depend on others. Check the project README for feature dependencies and status

- Treatments (`hms_treatment`) depend on consultations and patient records
- Day finalization depends on attendance status
- Calendar depends on attendance scheduling
- Session rows (`hms_session`) depend on treatment plans

## Future Features (Planned)

See the project README for planned features and roadmap. Don't implement these without coordination:

- Advanced session management
- Analytics dashboard
- Medical records system
- Enhanced mobile optimization

## Feature Requests

To propose new features:

1. Review [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) to understand business context
2. Check project README / roadmap to see if already planned
3. Verify it aligns with project scope (assessment center management)
4. Review [SETUP.md](mdc:docs/SETUP.md) and `src/features/README.md` for implementation guidelines
5. Consider implementation complexity and impact
